The paper presents a novel complex gated RNN architecture for deep learning, which is likely to fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of the complex gated RNN for time series and sequence processing, which could fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper demonstrates the performance of the complex gated RNN on a human motion prediction task, which could fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.SD) sub-categories.
